Description: Fragment of neck and flattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine cream-buff. Rectangular stamp. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Pencil '22'. Perhaps Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 128, 4, but a common type and the surface condition is not typically 'Naucratite'. From a die close to that of Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, CEALEX MA 0645.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0418)
Acquisition name: Donated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (possibly)
